Adoption has been a defining blessing in my life. I believe every child deserves a loving, stable, safe home, and to walk through life with unconditional love by their side. Sadly, many will never experience this, and on average 443,000 children are in the United States foster care system. @raise.the.future exists to ensure that children who have been removed from their home due to abuse and neglect grow up to reach their full potential in life, by connecting them to a loving family that is empowered to help them heal. 

By supporting @raise.the.future you are raising the bar for what it means to support vulnerable youth as they navigate life. Find out more by visiting raisethefuture.org  #adoption #fostering

node.text:
Onaqui

Please help stop this! I know that it can be hard to invest and hard to care if you don’t really know what’s going on. Why it’s going on. Or who it truly benefits but trust me when I tell you, none of the answers make any sense or are even remotely humane. All of us who have been fighting to stop this roundup have given it everything we’ve got and this is our 11th hour Hail Mary. Please. Please use your power, your voice to bombard the powers that be and implore them to stop this horrific and barbaric round up of our beloved Onaqui wild horse herd. Many of the mares have just had their foals…who will be trampled and killed if this proceeds. All of the herd will be terrorized and endangered, separated and left to either live and die in government holding pens, or even taken to auction where they will be sold to slaughter houses for horse meat. Take 5 minutes to email White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki:  jennifer.r.psaki@who.eop.gov and ask her to #stoptheroundup. You can even copy and paste this post to make it easier.  Thank you in advance for raising your voice on behalf of the voiceless!

node.text:
Sadly others will suffer the same fate as Aboo with the decision to keep access to LA shelters restricted indefinitely.

THE @jasonheiglfoundation POSITION ON THE CLOSED SHELTERS IN LOS ANGELES COUNTY

1.	Shelters are funded by the public and their tax dollars. We, as taxpayers, who pay for the shelters and their employees, have a right to see what takes place there and to physically be able to see all of the animals during normal working hours.

2.	The primary purpose of our shelters, the reason for their existence, is to find homes for the animals that are sheltered there. It is not to make things as easy as possible for the employees and staff.

3.	It is impossible for this purpose to be served well with the shelters closed to the public, rescues and potential adopters. By only permitting adopters and rescues in by appointment and only allowing them to see one animal during a visit, this is counterintuitive to what our shelter system was created to do.

4.	Under the present circumstances stated in #3, no animals should be euthanized unless they are suffering with serious medical problems. By severely limiting access to them and creating a situation where thousands will be passed over, good, adoptable dogs and cats will be euthanized.

5.	Baldwin Park, is one County shelter that we are aware of, now euthanizing for “lack of interest.” This claim borders on the absurd, considering it is now very difficult to even show any interest in a shelter animal. Quick, thoughtless intake pictures will help very few animals garner interest. In fact, they usually do the reverse.

6.	Considering all the above, the Jason Debus Heigl Foundation is now committed to using all of the resources available to us to ensure that shelters are reopened to the public, that this decision is reversed and that each and every shelter animal is given a fair opportunity to be adopted, rescued and ultimately placed in a forever home. 

Nancy and Katherine Heigl

node.text:
There are a billion wonderful things I could say about @joshbkelley as a man, and a billion more I could say about him as a father. I won’t try to list them all here, but suffice it to say…I am deeply deeply grateful for him. 

I won’t say I just got lucky, finding Josh, though I did. I won’t say it was just fate, though I believe it may have been. I won’t say that it’s always just love and fun and games, though more often then not it is. I won’t say that it’s not work, this family, this marriage, though it’s worth it. I will say there is no one. NO ONE. I would rather be in the trenches of parenthood with. There is no one I would rather celebrate the wins with. There is NO ONE I trust more to guide and encourage and support and love our children…or me for that matter, than him. Happy Father’s Day Josh. I hope that the best part of today is a quiet moment to yourself where the truth of your great and mighty success as a father and a man sinks in and you allow yourself to feel proud. Of all you have accomplished. Of all the love you so effortlessly pour forth. Of all the the laughter and safety and ease and peace our family revels in because of you. I love you. Thank you. You’ve made my dreams come true. ❤️

Please help me and @AnimalWellnessAction save our iconic American wild horses on the range. The Onaqui herd in Utah will soon be rounded up by @MyPublicLands in the coming weeks via helicopter chase. It’s a horrific injustice and these majestic symbols of our nation deserve better. Please take action now (link in bio) & ask @POTUS @SecDebHaaland @USInterior to stop the roundups. Visit www.SaveTheOnaqui.org #SaveTheOnaqui #WildHorses #StopTheRoundups #Horses
Photos: @WildHorsePhotoSafaris

node.text: Sharing some more of my art - this time of the digital variety! Please meet Gilbert and Gwendoline... and yes @joshbkelley is right, I'm kinda addicted to the Procreate app at the moment. Did I mention addiction? 🤣 ❤

node.text: @joshbkelley and I are having a glass of wine and talking about my art work. He has pushed the hell out of me to post some of my work. I’ve been too afraid to share it cause I’m just an amateur artist with passion and no real schooling...but he challenged me to face my fear and share. So...here’s a watercolor portrait of Adalaide that I added alcohol ink flowers to. So there @joshbkelley challenge accepted! #facingmyfears
